<br>
Or maybe it was just an accident.  Nobody meant to hurt that girl.  The player sure didn't say to himself, &quot;Gee, if I align my shot just just right, it should go right...over...there!&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm sure everyone fells horrible about the girl's death.  I'm sure the parents do want someone to blame.  It's part of the grieving process.  But accidents do happen.  We can't predict or prevent them.  They are not intentional.  That's why they are called accidents.  Some people just need to learn to take a little personal responsibility and stop whining and blaming other people when something goes wrong. <br>
<br>
Yes, it was a tragic death, not a casual &quot;oops.&quot;  The scope of the accident does not automatically mean there is blame to lay in places it would not normally be lain.<br>
<br>
My toaster has a huge warning on it that says, &quot;Warning, do not immerse in liquid,&quot; and &quot;Unplug before cleaning.&quot;  This is undoubtably because some idiot fried himself when he stuck the thing in a sink of water while it was still toasting his pop-tarts, and he sued the company for not having adequate instructions.  That would not be an accident.  That would be a candidate for the Darwin Awards.<br>
<br>
An accident is when you are walking down the street and a meteorite beans you over the head.  Or you are sitting at home, you swat a fly, knock over your can of soda, the soda falls onto the floor, spraying pop everywhere in a whirl of brown fizz, it scares the cat who then claws your friend's leg and he needs stiches.  Does the friend sue?  Apparently so, since it was your direct action that caused injury.  But for gods' sakes, it was an ACCIDENT. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.familjenguild.com/dspMember.php?Name=Hildie"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.familjenguild.com/images/logo/hildie.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I am not an NPC. When you hail me, I do not say, &quot;Greetings. I can [buff] you, [imbue gems], [enchant] items, or [combine] goods for you to sell.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showMessageRange?topicID=3168.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showMessageRange?topicID=3168.topic&start=41&stop=59>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showPrevMessage?topicID=3168.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showNextMessage?topicID=3168.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3168.topic&index=20><img src=http://members.cox.net/cbilyeu/tavern/notnice_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></t